dt-option.default:
        The default value for the `-init columns.searchPanes.hideCount` paramater is `false`. Meaning that as standard the count column will be included in the pane.


        As standard, SearchPanes will be displayed with the count column included in the table. However if the value of `-init columns.searchPanes.hideCount` is set to 'true' then the count column will no longer be displayed.

		This is useful as a styling option for those that do not want to include the count column. 

        The count column can be hidden for all of the panes by making use of the `-init searchPanes.hideCount`.





$(document).ready(function() {
    $('#example').DataTable( {
        searchPanes:true,
        columnDefs:[
            {
                searchPanes: {
                    hideCount: true,
                },
                targets: [4]
            }
        ]
    });
});



-init searchPanes.hideCount
